## Cloud Computing

| Name | Description | Funding Source | Contact |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **[Abaco](/research/tacc-research/abaco)** | *Abaco (Actor Based Containers) is a functions-as-a-service platform based on Linux container technology and the actor model for concurrent computation.* | NSF Award SI2-SSI 1740288 | Joe Stubbs [jstubbs@tacc.utexas.edu](mailto:jstubbs@tacc.utexas.edu) |
| **[Tapis](/research/tacc-research/tapis)** | *The Tapis Framework provides a hosted, unified web-based API for securely managing computational workloads across institutions so that experts can focus on their research instead of the technology needed to accomplish it.* | NSF Awards [#1931439](https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=1931439&HistoricalAwards=false) and [#1931575](https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=1931575&HistoricalAwards=false) | Joe Stubbs [jstubbs@tacc.utexas.edu](mailto:jstubbs@tacc.utexas.edu) |

